These are release notes for Altoros Heartbeat for Pivotal Platform.

## <a id="v1.2.1"></a> v1.2.1

**Release Date:** Apr 25, 2019

New features available in this release:

* Upgrades the stemcell to Ubuntu Xenial.

## <a id="v1.2.0"></a> v1.2.0

**Release Date:** Oct 19, 2018

New features available in this release:

* Requires stemcell 3586 series.
* BOSH DNS is enabled by default for Altoros Heartbeat components.
* Consul removed from the tile dependencies.

## <a id="v1.1.0"></a> v1.1.0

**Release Date:** May 30, 2018

New features available in this release:

* Added TCP Routing monitoring (Firehose and HAProxy metrics).
* Updated the existing dashboards and alerts for Diego.
* Updated the existing dashboards for the Cloud Foundry components.
* Added new dashboards for the Cloud Foundry components.
* A new version of the collectd BOSH add-on (v10.0.5).
* Added a description of the drill-down feature in the documentation.
* Added the option to disable SSL certificate verification for UAA and CC API endpoints for Grafana.
* Truncated the dashboard names ending with `with Logs`. Delete such dashboards, if you have any left.
* Added support for Pivotal Platform v2.0 and initial support for Pivotal Platform v2.1.
* Added OS-tuning properties.
* Moved a nozzle to a separate VM.
* Enabled a local cache for metrics requests.
* Changed a formula for a replication factor and added a property to override a replication factor.
* Made it possible to configure metrics storage schemas.
* Updated the existing dashboards for Services.
* Added dashboards for "MySQL for Pivotal Platform v1".
* Added Heartbeat self-alerts.
* Performance optimizations.

## <a id="v1.0.2"></a> v1.0.2

**Release Date:** October 25, 2017

Features included in this release:

* Concourse monitoring
* HAProxy monitoring
* Dashboards bootstrapping mechanism improvements
* Inactive metrics are stored for 30 days now by default

<p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong> Inactive metrics are stored for 30 days by default and will be removed after this period. If you need to store inactive metrics for a different period of time, please change the <strong>Days to keep inactive metrics</strong> parameter with the needed value on the <strong>Heartbeat Metrics Storage Configuration</strong> tab.</p>

## <a id="v1.0.1"></a> v1.0.1

**Release Date:** October 6, 2017

Features included in this release:

* Decreases the persistent disk space taken by the service frontend
* Improves description of properties in the tile configuration UI
* Fixes the RabbitMQ monitoring issue
* Adds support for syslog logs from both Metron and blackbox

<p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong> The service frontend no longer requires 100&nbsp;GB of persistent disk space.
   You can now downscale to 5&nbsp;GB.</p>

## <a id="v1.0.0"></a> v1.0.0

**Release Date:** September 18, 2017

Features included in this release:

* Support for a high availability mode of operation
* Back end and front end VMs are separated to improve flexibility and scalability
* New versions of components
* The Heartbeat URL is now `monitoring.%system-domain%`

Known issues in this release:

* Alerts are not enabled automatically after installation of the Altoros Heartbeat for Pivotal Platform tile.
  To [enable alerts](using.html#alerting-dashboards), open the **alerting** dashboard and click the save icon.

